Subject: [PATCH 1/4] =?UTF-8?q?AccessibilityAnalysis:=20add=20self-hosted?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20Valhalla=20isochrone=20backend=20(BACKLOG=20=C2=A73)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add a config-selectable routing backend so isochrones can come from a
self-hosted Valhalla instead of OpenRouteService, while keeping ORS as the
default/fallback. Designed as an additive change so it rebases cleanly onto
future upstream COSI releases (BACKLOG §2.5):

- New utils/requestIsochronesValhalla.js: one request per coordinate (Valhalla
  isochrones are single-origin), profile->costing mapping (driving-car->auto,
  cycling-regular->bicycle, foot-walking/wheelchair->pedestrian), s/m->min/km
  contour conversion, and response normalization back to the ORS feature shape
  ({group_index, value, center}, value in seconds/meters, ascending by value).
- utils/requestIsochrones.js: thin dispatch guard (serviceType === "valhalla")
  at the top; ORS body untouched.
- Thread serviceType through createIsochrones.js and the methodsAnalysis call.
- AccessibilityAnalysis.vue: backend-aware baseUrl (Valhalla <url>/isochrone,
  ORS <url>/v2/isochrones).
- state: new isochroneBackend flag (default "ors"; set "valhalla" in config.json
  and point serviceId at the Valhalla rest-service to switch).
- New unit spec covering conversions, request shape, normalization/ordering,
  multi-origin grouping, and error handling (7 tests, vitest).

